(1) Where, in respect of a tourist enterprise , the Board is satisfied that the tourist enterprise , its manager or servant has— (a) been convicted of an offence under this Act or of an offence relating to the operations of the tourist enterprise ; (b) contravened or failed to comply with the provisions of this Act, any regulations made hereunder or any directives issued under this Act; (c) contravened or failed to comply with any of the terms and conditions under which the tourist enterprise was to be established, maintained or operated; (d) failed to pay the appropriate fee for the licence or authorisation ; or (e) obtained the licence or authorisation by fraud, deliberate misrepresentation or other illegal means; it may revoke the licence or authorisation of such tourist enterprise .
